data.event: It included the area which is now part of Canberra and as far north as Lake George and Yass.

event.title: was transferred to the Commonwealth government in 1909

data.event: A large area of the county was transferred to the Commonwealth government in 1909 in the Seat of Government Acceptance Act to make part of the Australian Capital Territory, along with land in Cowley County.

event.title: is mentioned in the Seat of Government Acceptance Act of 1909

data.event: This is mentioned in the Seat of Government Acceptance Act of 1909.
